[Student "S"]
{When SOUTH opens 2\C NORTH has enough strength (9 points) for a positive response. But, 
because her suit is \Ds, she must jump to 3\D.

SOUTH thinks slam and uses Blackwood to discover that NORTH holds one Ace. 

That's all NORTH needs to know to bid 6\D.}

